                            <comment id="487388" author="JIRAUSER18604" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2026 19:54:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will analyze the test and fix the issue&lt;br/&gt;
== test migration ==&lt;br/&gt;
/tmp/t32/mnt/lustre /usr/lib64/lustre/tests&lt;br/&gt;
lfs migrate: cb_migrate_mdt_fini: error completing migration of ./.fscrypt: Directory not empty (39)&lt;br/&gt;
/usr/lib64/lustre/tests&lt;br/&gt;
 conf-sanity test_32c: @@@@@@ FAIL: migrate MDT1 failed&lt;br/&gt;
thanks Andreas&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="487384" author="adilger" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2026 19:31:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this patch has exposed an issue related to migrating a directory with encrypted files in it. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like the patch is repeatedly failing conf-sanity test_32c during file migration.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18348&quot; title=&quot;interop: conf-sanity test_32b: FAIL: sha1sum verification failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18348&quot;&gt;LU-18348&lt;/a&gt; relates to interop issues with accessing the key while calculating the sha1sum of the file, but this is failing during the migrate step. I suspect it is also failing without this patch, but is silently ignored because no error is being returned:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== test migration ==
/tmp/t32/mnt/lustre /usr/lib64/lustre/tests
lfs migrate: cb_migrate_mdt_fini: error completing migration of ./.fscrypt: Directory not empty (39)
/usr/lib64/lustre/tests
 conf-sanity test_32c: @@@@@@ FAIL: migrate MDT1 failed
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
